#X text 57 90 [keytrack2] is like [keytrack] but you can set different parameters up and below the reference point(s). It maps MIDI pitch input from a keyboard and outputs a function you can use to control things like a filter cutoff. The output is pitch ratio value. By default we have MIDI pitch 60 (middle C) as an unaltered reference point (ratio 1). The tracking amount affects the mapping amount \, where a minimum value of 0 sets no tracking (all ratios are equal to 1)., f 72;
